New Records: Spencer Strider achieved his 17th win, setting a major league record.
Matt Olson tied the franchise's single-season home run record with his 51st homer.
Key Match Events: Kirby Yates struck out Brandon Marsh to end the game, and the Braves celebrated with a mob near the mound as Phillies fans booed.
The game was significant as it was played on the same field where the Phillies had eliminated the Braves in the NLDS the previous year.
Pre-Game Insights: The Braves had a magic number of two entering the game and were on pace to win 106 games, tying a franchise record.
The Braves had a 17-game lead in the division and were dominant in September.
Post-Match Reflections: The Braves celebrated with sparkling wine and beer in the visitors' clubhouse, marking a special win after last season's playoff loss.
Manager Brian Snitker expressed pride in the team's resilience.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves were leading the MLB in wins and had a strong lineup with multiple players reaching significant milestones.
The Phillies were leading the NL wild card race and could face the Braves in the playoffs.
